The paper deals with computational complexity issues related to voter control problems in elections, which are a topic of interest in computational social choice. Therefore, cs.GT (Computational Social Choice) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and the study of combinatorial structures, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of heuristics and approximation algorithms, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
